WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:15.510 --> 00:02:17.238
Keep going!

3
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:19.240
Bring it on down!

4
00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:20.575
-That's it!
-Come on!

5
00:02:20.599 --> 00:02:22.076
-Keep moving!
-Back into it.

6
00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:26.164
Three more in here.

7
00:02:28.815 --> 00:02:30.776
Three more in there.

8
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:32.944
You. go with them!

9
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:35.447
Two more in here.

10
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:40.994
Two more in here.

11
00:02:48.627 --> 00:02:50.629
You three. in this one.

12
00:02:52.464 --> 00:02:53.715
Oh. please. please.

13
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:57.111
Our home. it's...
it's already crowded.

14
00:02:57.135 --> 00:02:59.781
There's 15.000 of us.

15
00:02:59.805 --> 00:03:01.223
Be glad you only got three.

16
00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:06.978
-Maybe crowded ain't so bad.
-Mind yourself.

17
00:03:08.230 --> 00:03:10.958
You don't like it.
go and carp to Lord Ormund.

18
00:03:10.982 --> 00:03:12.317
See what good it does you.

19
00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:29.519
It is only regarding
the lodging situation. my lord.

20
00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:32.146
You are unhappy with
your lodgings. Lord Footly?

21
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.482
It is only that we are very fond
of our ancestral home.

22
00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:36.466
You are sleeping
in our bedchamber.

23
00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:39.696
You bent the knee to the
pretender. Rhaenyra Targaryen.

24
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:41.698
did you not. Lady Footly?

25
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:43.491
We did.

26
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:44.909
Then mayhaps I should remind you

27
00:03:44.933 --> 00:03:46.869
that the wage of treason
is death.

28
00:03:46.893 --> 00:03:48.413
We do not seek conflict.
my lord.

29
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:50.832
Tumbleton has no battlements.

30
00:03:50.856 --> 00:03:52.542
Our people know only trade.

31
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:55.378
We never thought to see war.

32
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.338
So. you swore to her
out of fear.

33
00:03:57.362 --> 00:03:59.948
We swore because
she is the queen.

34
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:04.745
Is she?

35
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:17.215
Or is she a bitch with a dragon?

36
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:23.698
My purpose is to restore
the rightful line

37
00:04:23.722 --> 00:04:24.973
to the Iron Throne.

38
00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:28.560
It follows from that
that I must be well rested.

39
00:04:30.061 --> 00:04:34.399
It follows from that that I
must have acceptable lodgings.

40
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:38.629
I will ensure that my men
remain on their best behavior

41
00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:40.238
whilst in your town.

42
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:44.451
Provided. of course...

43
00:04:46.661 --> 00:04:48.890
That you remain on yours.

44
00:04:48.914 --> 00:04:50.248
See them out.

45
00:04:52.834 --> 00:04:54.211
Don't.

46
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:56.272
When dealing with those
beneath you.

47
00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:58.316
you must be fair. but firm.

48
00:04:58.340 --> 00:04:59.758
Yes. sire.

49
00:05:02.844 --> 00:05:04.071
My prince.

50
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:06.407
My lord. a raven
from Storm's End

51
00:05:06.431 --> 00:05:09.142
carrying more excuses
from Lord Borros Baratheon.

52
00:05:16.399 --> 00:05:19.045
That lackwit sealed a marriage
pact between Prince Aemond

53
00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:22.006
and one of his horse-faced
daughters.

54
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:23.966
And yet. where is he now?

55
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:26.093
Send another raven
that he can understand.

56
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:28.620
This one mayhaps with drawings
rather than letters.

57
00:05:34.417 --> 00:05:36.211
What word from Harrenhal?

58
00:05:38.421 --> 00:05:42.634
If Vhagar does not
come. our defenses will not hold.

59
00:05:48.431 --> 00:05:50.267
Do not be disheartened. Daeron.

60
00:05:51.977 --> 00:05:53.645
Your brother will join us soon.

61
00:05:58.650 --> 00:06:01.170
<i>Why seize Tumbleton?</i>

62
00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:04.215
It's no stronghold.
It's a market town.

63
00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:07.468
Its lord is meek.
Its walls are poorly defended.

64
00:06:07.492 --> 00:06:09.846
Hightower may as well
paint a rondel on his chest.

65
00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:10.871
Why?

66
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:14.165
Does he mean to somehow
win their support?

67
00:06:16.251 --> 00:06:19.146
He dares me
to rain fire down on a seat

68
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.315
that raised my banner.

69
00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:23.693
And the realm would name me
"Maegor Returned."

70
00:06:23.717 --> 00:06:25.653
They'd rise up against me.

71
00:06:25.677 --> 00:06:28.322
And the same gods
who delivered me to the throne

72
00:06:28.346 --> 00:06:29.699
would rightly cast me down.

73
00:06:29.723 --> 00:06:32.410
If I may.

74
00:06:32.434 --> 00:06:34.328
Your Grace.
Prince Daemon's river host

75
00:06:34.352 --> 00:06:36.664
marches on King's Landing.

76
00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:39.041
Tumbleton is not much further.

77
00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:41.419
If his men were
to go there instead...

78
00:06:41.443 --> 00:06:44.422
Mm. it would not be bloodless.

79
00:06:44.446 --> 00:06:47.532
but it would be far more
merciful than sending dragons.

80
00:06:49.534 --> 00:06:51.178
We march on the town

81
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.705
and root out the Hightowers
house to house.

82
00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.435
It's a good scheme.

83
00:06:57.459 --> 00:06:59.085
Send orders to Lord Tully.

84
00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:02.422
Uh. Orwyle?

85
00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:07.302
For as long as you remain
loyal and useful...

86
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.531
you may take your place
at my council

87
00:07:10.555 --> 00:07:12.390
and retain the title
of Grand Maester.

88
00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:18.205
The castle's ravens
remain your charge.

89
00:07:18.229 --> 00:07:21.029
but the Lady Mysaria should be kept
informed of the comings and goings.

90
00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:22.776
Ah.

91
00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:26.738
Relics of a dead regime.

92
00:07:27.906 --> 00:07:29.550
Mm.

93
00:07:29.574 --> 00:07:32.303
It will take the Rivermen weeks
to reach Tumbleton.

94
00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:34.805
Let us send a dragon
to keep vigil.

95
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:37.266
Ormund may have
the town under siege.

96
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:40.311
but he shall not leave
except I remove him.

97
00:07:40.335 --> 00:07:45.107
In the meantime. we have.
uh. urgent matters at home.

98
00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:47.610
We have secured
some small store of oil

99
00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:49.434
-for the markets. but...
-Where is the Hand?

100
00:07:51.388 --> 00:07:54.265
Gods. this council's thin.

101
00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:00.438
Name a Master of Coin.

102
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:05.002
The people will soon discover
our lacking resources.

103
00:08:05.026 --> 00:08:07.070
They can blame him.

104
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:14.095
Investigate
Ser Torrhen Manderly.

105
00:08:14.119 --> 00:08:15.930
He's intrigued me.

106
00:08:15.954 --> 00:08:18.790
If he's fit. let the gold be his
concern as well as Daemon's.

107
00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:22.961
Mine shall be Ormund Hightower.

108
00:08:26.631 --> 00:08:28.359
I know him as well as you.

109
00:08:28.383 --> 00:08:30.468
I... I doubt that.

110
00:08:31.469 --> 00:08:34.305
Viserys warded your son to him.
I've never met the man.

111
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:39.954
I knew him very little.
a long time ago.

112
00:08:39.978 --> 00:08:42.832
After my father took me to
court. I rarely saw Oldtown.

113
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:44.190
Tell me what you do know.

114
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.990
He sees himself as a scholar.

115
00:08:53.116 --> 00:08:54.969
He studies the histories.

116
00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:58.222
he collects tapestries.
writes ballads.

117
00:08:58.246 --> 00:09:00.206
despises the ignorant
and uncouth.

118
00:09:01.624 --> 00:09:03.477
When we were young.
Gwayne thought him cruel.

119
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:05.813
but Gwayne thought that of many.

120
00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:07.172
How is he with Daeron?

121
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:11.736
Fatherly. I'm told.

122
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:13.887
Daeron was only a babe
when he took him to ward.

123
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:16.514
What is it?

124
00:09:17.265 --> 00:09:18.826
Oh. look at this.

125
00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:22.020
Did it pain you to have
to send your child away?

126
00:09:26.691 --> 00:09:28.401
It was my choice.

127
00:09:29.360 --> 00:09:30.361
Why?

128
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:38.745
I bore Viserys three Targaryens.

129
00:09:40.246 --> 00:09:42.040
But with the last. my last...

130
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.210
I wanted him to be a Hightower.

131
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.190
In truth. I'm glad
I waged that battle.

132
00:09:49.214 --> 00:09:51.382
seeing now what came
of our other sons.

133
00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:55.386
Perhaps sending Daeron away
was my truest act of motherhood.

134
00:09:58.306 --> 00:09:59.909
Though I do not know
now what fate

135
00:09:59.933 --> 00:10:01.434
that choice has consigned him.

136
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:11.820
You know I would
have spared him.

137
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:24.082
He has a sensitivity to odors.

138
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:26.918
Ormund.

139
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:29.963
A very strong one.

140
00:10:32.715 --> 00:10:35.069
My Lord Hand.
the queen has requested

141
00:10:35.093 --> 00:10:36.904
your presence
at her small council.

142
00:10:36.928 --> 00:10:39.615
I'm her Hand. not her mouth.

143
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:41.909
Leave the talking to those
who relish it.

144
00:10:41.933 --> 00:10:43.410
Shall I return
with this message?

145
00:10:43.434 --> 00:10:44.870
That you refuse the queen?

146
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:47.581
Rather that I serve
more effectively.

147
00:10:47.605 --> 00:10:50.251
Her strength lies
in dragons now.

148
00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:52.443
She has less need
of a man of the sea.

149
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:57.758
But my son shall attend her
in my stead.

150
00:10:57.782 --> 00:10:59.450
You certainly look the part.

151
00:11:00.952 --> 00:11:03.055
I am not a creature
of the court.

152
00:11:03.079 --> 00:11:04.807
I don't know what I'm doing.

153
00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:07.167
There is great opportunity
for you there.

154
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:10.896
I cannot give you legitimacy.

155
00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:13.464
but I can give you the chance
to better yourself.

156
00:11:18.469 --> 00:11:22.056
Anger is not something that can
be ended with a blade. my lord.

157
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:27.854
Move out!

158
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.366
Come on!

159
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:38.299
My boy.

160
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:40.718
I'm here.

161
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:43.888
I'm here.

162
00:12:47.976 --> 00:12:50.103
It's a penny
to touch the dragon.

163
00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:54.792
Nothing's free in these woods.

164
00:12:54.816 --> 00:12:57.086
He can sit the saddle
for a halfgroat.

165
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.712
Touch will suffice.

166
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:00.113
-Mm.
-Thank you.

167
00:13:04.409 --> 00:13:07.137
We seek shelter.

168
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:09.098
Which way to Rook's Rest?

169
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:11.225
He's got both hands on him.

170
00:13:11.249 --> 00:13:12.583
That's two touches.

171
00:13:30.977 --> 00:13:32.854
What's wrong with your leg?

172
00:13:37.108 --> 00:13:41.195
You can kill a man of the Faith
for a few pennies. if you wish.

173
00:13:42.780 --> 00:13:45.426
Though I doubt the gods
would look kindly upon it.

174
00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:47.511
You don't look like a septon.

175
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:48.995
He's alive.

176
00:13:53.458 --> 00:13:56.103
I know it.
He's alive. he must be.

177
00:13:56.127 --> 00:13:58.188
-Sunfyre.
-There. there. Gregor.

178
00:13:58.212 --> 00:13:59.773
Wake up. Sunfyre. I'm here.

179
00:13:59.797 --> 00:14:01.942
Let us trouble these
good folk no further. hm?

180
00:14:01.966 --> 00:14:04.028
Wake up. Sunfyre. I'm here.

181
00:14:04.052 --> 00:14:05.345
Simple.

182
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.492
What's he saying?

183
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:12.703
Sunfyre. come back to me.

184
00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:14.913
Wake up. I'm here.
I know you're in there.

185
00:14:14.937 --> 00:14:17.708
We must tarry no longer.
The danger is great.

186
00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:20.002
I am very sorry.

187
00:14:20.026 --> 00:14:22.362
but you must accept
what is before you.

188
00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:26.383
Wake up.

189
00:14:26.407 --> 00:14:29.077
You wanted to see him.
you've seen him.

190
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:32.973
-He's dead.
-No.

191
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:35.017
Will you stay and rot with him?

192
00:14:36.584 --> 00:14:39.379
Will you get up and live?

193
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:57.206
Are you lost?

194
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:03.754
Where is the castellan?

195
00:16:06.424 --> 00:16:07.758
Slain.

196
00:16:08.593 --> 00:16:09.969
He who succeeds him then.

197
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.490
Slain.

198
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:15.475
And the one
who succeeds him as well.

199
00:16:16.934 --> 00:16:18.352
And who are you?

200
00:16:19.270 --> 00:16:21.457
A steward. of a sort.

201
00:16:21.481 --> 00:16:24.084
It's the best you can do
at the moment.

202
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:25.860
This is the Hand of the King.

203
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.154
We seek the Prince Aemond.

204
00:16:30.114 --> 00:16:32.116
As I'm sure do many.

205
00:16:35.620 --> 00:16:37.931
He was meant to meet us here.

206
00:16:37.955 --> 00:16:39.183
If you know where he is.

207
00:16:39.207 --> 00:16:41.643
I'd advise you
to be forthcoming.

208
00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:47.256
He was here.

209
00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:51.528
He seized the castle after
Prince Daemon abandoned it.

210
00:16:51.552 --> 00:16:54.281
but when he learned that
Rhaenyra took King's Landing.

211
00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:57.141
-he and his dragon fled.
-W-When Rhaenyra took King's Landing?

212
00:17:03.022 --> 00:17:04.315
Oh. my.

213
00:17:05.566 --> 00:17:07.026
Oh. you didn't know.

214
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.968
We've scoured the area.
my Lord Hand.

215
00:17:14.992 --> 00:17:17.221
There is sign
of a large dragon nest

216
00:17:17.245 --> 00:17:18.663
but it has been abandoned.

217
00:17:19.664 --> 00:17:22.250
Prince Aemond
may indeed have fled.

218
00:17:32.843 --> 00:17:34.530
King's Landing has fallen.

219
00:17:34.554 --> 00:17:37.741
Aegon is dead. our queens
are both in chains.

220
00:17:37.765 --> 00:17:40.035
and we are here alone

221
00:17:40.059 --> 00:17:42.228
with a meager army
and no dragon.

222
00:17:44.188 --> 00:17:46.023
We have the enemy
just where we want them.

223
00:17:48.568 --> 00:17:50.212
Aemond would not desert me.

224
00:17:50.236 --> 00:17:53.030
And yet he's not here. is he?

225
00:17:55.074 --> 00:17:56.826
Let us send a raven
to Tumbleton.

226
00:17:57.743 --> 00:17:59.846
Alert my cousin of this news

227
00:17:59.870 --> 00:18:02.391
and our intent
to join our strength to his.

228
00:18:02.415 --> 00:18:04.226
Ormund is a stiff-necked
windbag.

229
00:18:04.250 --> 00:18:05.686
but he's neither
craven nor stupid.

230
00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:08.045
He will have
some canny plot afoot.

231
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:12.466
No.

232
00:18:18.222 --> 00:18:21.183
The game is
played. Ser Criston. and it is lost.

233
00:18:22.184 --> 00:18:24.121
What possible profit
is there in pursuing it?

234
00:18:28.899 --> 00:18:31.962
You noble ilk conceive this
all a great game. don't you?

235
00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:34.631
To win. to lose.
go home to a feather bed.

236
00:18:36.741 --> 00:18:39.052
I was a foot soldier.
Did you know that?

237
00:18:39.076 --> 00:18:40.554
Steward's son.

238
00:18:40.578 --> 00:18:43.390
All my father had was at
the pleasure of Lord Dondarrion.

239
00:18:43.414 --> 00:18:45.791
When his favor failed.
all we had melted away.

240
00:18:49.086 --> 00:18:50.963
My father died of sorrow.

241
00:18:51.922 --> 00:18:53.924
There is no home
for one like me.

242
00:18:56.594 --> 00:18:58.596
Not while Rhaenyra
sits the throne.

243
00:19:01.932 --> 00:19:03.476
Our task is simple.

244
00:19:04.852 --> 00:19:06.663
Keep the river scum
from reaching King's Landing.

245
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:08.457
Give Ormund time
to swell his ranks.

246
00:19:08.481 --> 00:19:10.834
Their army is ten times
our size.

247
00:19:10.858 --> 00:19:12.085
Twenty.

248
00:19:12.109 --> 00:19:13.778
But let us attack it...

249
00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:16.614
as the scorpion does the ox.

250
00:19:19.408 --> 00:19:22.929
Let us become wraiths
with fear as our standard.

251
00:19:22.953 --> 00:19:24.473
Strike from the quiet
and the darkness.

252
00:19:24.497 --> 00:19:26.540
Our fight will not be clean.
but it will be pure.

253
00:19:28.376 --> 00:19:29.627
We'll be man-to-man.

254
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.465
And it will be free
from dragons.

255
00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:42.306
-Ser Edgar!
-We'll delay them at most.

256
00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:47.120
-It will not change their course.
-Perhaps not.

257
00:19:47.144 --> 00:19:49.414
But it is as you said.
Ser Gwayne.

258
00:19:49.438 --> 00:19:52.983
We must cling to our honor.
lest we become beasts ourselves.

259
00:20:18.092 --> 00:20:19.569
Who goes there?

260
00:20:19.593 --> 00:20:21.029
Alyn of Hull.

261
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:23.013
I'll see him. Come.

262
00:20:25.015 --> 00:20:27.160
Your Grace.

263
00:20:27.184 --> 00:20:30.038
Lord Corlys has ridden out
by the Dragon Gate

264
00:20:30.062 --> 00:20:32.565
to hunt the Triarchy raiders
that plague our trade.

265
00:20:34.525 --> 00:20:36.777
He has able men who could
lead that campaign.

266
00:20:38.279 --> 00:20:42.199
While his queen struggles
to restore a broken kingdom.

267
00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:48.038
Your Grace. uh. if I may.

268
00:20:49.582 --> 00:20:52.936
My lord father has lost much

269
00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:55.212
and found himself thwarted.

270
00:20:56.172 --> 00:21:00.050
A fight is mayhaps
what he needs.

271
00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:03.929
Hm.

272
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:07.725
Oh.

273
00:21:08.768 --> 00:21:10.078
My father's life's work.

274
00:21:10.102 --> 00:21:12.855
a recreation of the seat
of Old Valyria.

275
00:21:14.565 --> 00:21:16.776
A reminder to him.
I think. that. um...

276
00:21:18.861 --> 00:21:20.780
even great dynasties fall.

277
00:21:21.906 --> 00:21:24.325
That the crown should
never rest easy on his head.

278
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:29.723
There were those who whispered
that my father was weak.

279
00:21:29.747 --> 00:21:32.893
But. um.
seeing through his eyes.

280
00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:34.895
I can only marvel

281
00:21:34.919 --> 00:21:36.921
at how he kept it
all in balance for so long.

282
00:21:38.422 --> 00:21:41.234
Fathers have
a maddening capacity

283
00:21:41.258 --> 00:21:44.070
to at once inspire and incense.

284
00:21:44.094 --> 00:21:46.156
Don't you think?

285
00:21:48.599 --> 00:21:50.351
Gods. they are incessant.

286
00:21:52.269 --> 00:21:54.814
And thanks to Aegon.
all the rat catchers are dead.

287
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:58.192
On board ship. we kept cats.

288
00:22:00.611 --> 00:22:03.656
Steel yourself.

289
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:08.160
We must guard our intents
whilst I quietly

290
00:22:09.703 --> 00:22:12.057
investigate hiring a ship.

291
00:22:12.081 --> 00:22:14.935
This is Cole's garrison.
They owe allegiance to me.

292
00:22:14.959 --> 00:22:16.585
This is no garrison.

293
00:22:17.586 --> 00:22:20.464
You must presume these men hold
allegiance only to themselves.

294
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:29.223
We cannot tarry here long.

295
00:23:01.171 --> 00:23:03.924
Good day. friend.
We seek food and shelter.

296
00:23:06.010 --> 00:23:09.030
Like many here gathered. we
are the dispossessed of the war.

297
00:23:09.054 --> 00:23:11.056
You Riverfolk?

298
00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:16.228
I fucking hate Riverfolk.

299
00:23:16.896 --> 00:23:19.249
We hail from Sharp Point.

300
00:23:19.273 --> 00:23:21.025
Prince Aemond burned it
to the ground.

301
00:23:22.526 --> 00:23:23.944
W-w-with his d...

302
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:30.367
-How'd you get out?
-We nearly didn't.

303
00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:35.039
As you can see.

304
00:23:36.749 --> 00:23:38.375
Hm.

305
00:23:46.967 --> 00:23:49.195
Well...

306
00:23:49.219 --> 00:23:51.239
We're too many.

307
00:23:51.263 --> 00:23:52.640
Fuck off.

308
00:23:53.891 --> 00:23:55.392
I have some coin.

309
00:24:10.032 --> 00:24:13.386
You can earn a tent
if you're ready to work.

310
00:24:13.410 --> 00:24:14.763
Have you got a trade?

311
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:16.431
I have some knowledge of herbs.

312
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.892
and. uh. I can read a little.

313
00:24:18.916 --> 00:24:20.084
Mm.

314
00:24:23.253 --> 00:24:24.814
Maybe you'll be useful.

315
00:24:24.838 --> 00:24:27.233
I have the command around here.

316
00:24:27.257 --> 00:24:30.820
Oh. that much is clear. my lord.

317
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:32.513
Tangletongue works the latrines.

318
00:24:33.806 --> 00:24:36.392
Collects piss for the tanners.
shit for the farmers.

319
00:24:37.935 --> 00:24:39.955
This one can help him.

320
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:41.414
Separate buckets.

321
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:44.250
Mix it up. they won't pay.

322
00:24:44.274 --> 00:24:47.337
I won't touch
the fucking latrines...

323
00:24:47.361 --> 00:24:49.422
J-Just do as they say. Gregor.

324
00:24:49.446 --> 00:24:51.216
-For now. hm?
-I can read just as well as he can.

325
00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:53.593
Tangletongue and Mangleface.

326
00:24:58.122 --> 00:24:59.933
-You'll be good together.
-I-It's not bad...

327
00:24:59.957 --> 00:25:02.397
-Don't fucking touch me.
-once you're used to it. brother.

328
00:25:03.460 --> 00:25:04.962
Come on.

329
00:25:07.506 --> 00:25:09.192
Come on.

330
00:25:09.216 --> 00:25:11.486
Fuck off!

331
00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:21.663
I think we'll have
a nice time here tonight.

332
00:25:21.687 --> 00:25:26.126
We'll make merry tonight.
It'll be better than Honeyholt.

333
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:38.829
Wait.

334
00:25:45.836 --> 00:25:48.255
I need to inspect the goods.

335
00:25:56.722 --> 00:25:58.849
Go and fetch some rosemary.

336
00:26:05.189 --> 00:26:06.690
Come on.

337
00:26:13.197 --> 00:26:15.425
Don't touch her!
Take your hands off of her!

338
00:26:25.375 --> 00:26:26.895
Get them out of here!
Get them out!

339
00:26:26.919 --> 00:26:29.588
Get your hands off my
brother. you Hightower...

340
00:26:38.055 --> 00:26:39.807
Ser Hugh Hammer. Your Grace.

341
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:43.203
Ser Hugh. I assure you.

342
00:26:43.227 --> 00:26:45.979
when there is news of a house.
you will be sent for.

343
00:26:47.523 --> 00:26:50.960
I understand that Ser Ulf
is to be sent to Tumbleton.

344
00:26:50.984 --> 00:26:53.546
-He is.
-If it pleases Your Grace.

345
00:26:53.570 --> 00:26:55.948
I offer to take the watch
on Vermithor.

346
00:26:58.075 --> 00:27:00.261
Your wife is at Tumbleton.
is she not?

347
00:27:00.285 --> 00:27:01.846
Ser Ulf has no stake
in the matter.

348
00:27:01.870 --> 00:27:03.413
Send me. because I do.

349
00:27:04.414 --> 00:27:07.126
I will not tire of watching
when one I love is below.

350
00:27:10.838 --> 00:27:12.273
Take it in turn between you.

351
00:27:12.297 --> 00:27:14.734
Keep watch on the town
and on each other.

352
00:27:14.758 --> 00:27:16.361
You may take the first post.

353
00:27:16.385 --> 00:27:18.095
See that Ulf is alerted
to the plan.

354
00:27:20.055 --> 00:27:21.473
Your Grace.

355
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:31.483
Disgusting.

356
00:27:35.445 --> 00:27:37.114
What's it say?

357
00:27:40.492 --> 00:27:42.035
"Queen of Bastards."

358
00:27:43.245 --> 00:27:46.540
Hightower loyalists trying
to fight a war they lost.

359
00:27:53.297 --> 00:27:55.942
So. he has returned.

360
00:27:59.469 --> 00:28:01.281
-Come on!
-Come on.

361
00:28:01.305 --> 00:28:03.324
-Ah! Good evening. ser!
-Hey!

362
00:28:03.348 --> 00:28:06.870
Ulf. the Dragonlord! Hey. hey.

363
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:08.621
More god than man.

364
00:28:08.645 --> 00:28:12.041
Hey. will you honor your friends
with a round of drinks. my lord?

365
00:28:12.065 --> 00:28:14.252
The price keeps rising.
we can't keep up.

366
00:28:14.276 --> 00:28:16.129
-Tell him.
-For everyone.

367
00:28:16.153 --> 00:28:17.797
Hear that?

368
00:28:17.821 --> 00:28:21.992
Drinks for everyone!

369
00:28:25.495 --> 00:28:27.390
-He broke my arm.
-That one broke my nose.

370
00:28:27.414 --> 00:28:29.184
-He attacked my sister.
-You call yourself soldiers. This is a disgrace.

371
00:28:29.208 --> 00:28:30.968
-The children are terrified.
-What is this?

372
00:28:32.544 --> 00:28:34.689
You said your men
were honorable.

373
00:28:34.713 --> 00:28:36.048
This one has sinned.

374
00:28:39.176 --> 00:28:41.321
I was billeted
at the smithy. my lord.

375
00:28:41.345 --> 00:28:44.157
But the smith didn't like it.

376
00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:46.558
Mayhaps he resents
the imposition.

377
00:28:47.601 --> 00:28:49.728
Or mayhaps he is loyal
to Rhaenyra.

378
00:28:50.687 --> 00:28:51.998
But he struck me.

379
00:28:52.022 --> 00:28:54.000
My lord. Now. if it please you.

380
00:28:54.024 --> 00:28:55.460
we bear you no ill will.

381
00:28:55.484 --> 00:28:57.921
But this man went
to ravish my sister

382
00:28:57.945 --> 00:29:00.715
and then broke my wife's arm
when she tried to stop him.

383
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:02.508
She is a weaver.

384
00:29:02.532 --> 00:29:04.368
We need what little she earns.

385
00:29:05.535 --> 00:29:07.847
-Is this true?
-No. my lord.

386
00:29:07.871 --> 00:29:09.432
-Liar!
-Look at this woman's arm.

387
00:29:09.456 --> 00:29:11.434
-She attacked me.
-Is there no safety

388
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:12.852
-in our houses anymore?
-She called me a cunt!

389
00:29:12.876 --> 00:29:14.544
I will have calm.

390
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:21.444
-What is your name?
-Garrick. my lord.

391
00:29:21.468 --> 00:29:22.862
of Whitegrove.

392
00:29:22.886 --> 00:29:24.888
Garrick of Whitegrove.

393
00:29:25.973 --> 00:29:27.849
You have violated guest right.

394
00:29:28.558 --> 00:29:30.536
You have debauched yourself
upon a woman

395
00:29:30.560 --> 00:29:32.205
and injured another.

396
00:29:32.229 --> 00:29:34.249
Your punishment
will fit your crime.

397
00:29:34.273 --> 00:29:35.875
You will be gelded.

398
00:29:35.899 --> 00:29:39.212
And you will
have your own arm broken.

399
00:29:39.236 --> 00:29:40.463
You may remain in my service.

400
00:29:40.487 --> 00:29:42.632
but trespass again.
and you will hang.

401
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:45.218
My lord. I have a wife.

402
00:29:45.242 --> 00:29:47.470
Oh! My lord!

403
00:29:47.494 --> 00:29:48.930
-Come on!
-No!

404
00:29:48.954 --> 00:29:51.415
See them home. Have a
maester tend to their wounds.

405
00:29:52.457 --> 00:29:53.667
No!

406
00:29:54.668 --> 00:29:55.919
My lord!

407
00:29:57.337 --> 00:30:00.590
We must keep a firm grip.
Tensions are high.

408
00:30:01.591 --> 00:30:04.737
Lawlessness and disorder
claw at our gates.

409
00:30:04.761 --> 00:30:06.013
Yes. sire.

410
00:30:15.897 --> 00:30:17.333
<i>I wish to see
all correspondence</i>

411
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:19.419
between the Red Keep
and Ormund Hightower

412
00:30:19.443 --> 00:30:20.777
since my father's death.

413
00:30:21.486 --> 00:30:22.612
Your Grace.

414
00:30:25.615 --> 00:30:28.177
How much control
do the Hightowers

415
00:30:28.201 --> 00:30:29.971
exert over the Faith?

416
00:30:29.995 --> 00:30:34.100
Well. they endowed the
building of the Starry Sept

417
00:30:34.124 --> 00:30:36.269
and Oldtown was their seat for.

418
00:30:36.293 --> 00:30:39.188
well. centuries before
the Conquest.

419
00:30:39.212 --> 00:30:41.941
The Seven are as intrinsic
to the Hightower fabric

420
00:30:41.965 --> 00:30:45.028
as. well. dragons are
to House Targaryen.

421
00:30:45.052 --> 00:30:46.946
But control. I think not.

422
00:30:46.970 --> 00:30:50.015
The Faith is too proud
to allow such influence.

423
00:30:51.975 --> 00:30:54.561
The. uh. the High Septon
has refused to anoint me.

424
00:30:56.813 --> 00:31:00.192
The Faith clings tightly
to its separate powers.

425
00:31:03.153 --> 00:31:07.407
If I may be so bold
to ask Your Grace...

426
00:31:08.325 --> 00:31:09.719
does it matter?

427
00:31:09.743 --> 00:31:11.971
-Wh...
-Your Grace sits the throne.

428
00:31:11.995 --> 00:31:15.058
Your people have welcomed
you back as a liberator.

429
00:31:15.082 --> 00:31:16.601
Your dragons rule the skies.

430
00:31:16.625 --> 00:31:19.336
Are these not symbols
of power enough?

431
00:31:20.712 --> 00:31:23.274
Perhaps I could remove him.

432
00:31:23.298 --> 00:31:25.985
The monarch has ever had
some influence

433
00:31:26.009 --> 00:31:27.987
in the... the naming
of the High Septon.

434
00:31:28.011 --> 00:31:30.990
but to remove him altogether
would surely...

435
00:31:31.014 --> 00:31:34.017
incite the Faith.
and therefore the faithful.

436
00:31:36.186 --> 00:31:38.522
Unless you were
considering a more. uh...

437
00:31:40.690 --> 00:31:42.359
permanent removal.

438
00:31:44.361 --> 00:31:46.214
I never thought you
so bloodthirsty. Orwyle.

439
00:31:46.238 --> 00:31:48.257
-Ah.
-Rather impressed.

440
00:31:48.281 --> 00:31:49.842
Alas. no.

441
00:31:49.866 --> 00:31:51.886
Bring Ormund's letters
once you have collated them.

442
00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:55.598
There's been no word from
Prince Daemon on his progress?

443
00:31:55.622 --> 00:31:57.374
None as yet. Your Grace.

444
00:32:03.213 --> 00:32:04.524
I had
thought never to see you

445
00:32:04.548 --> 00:32:07.026
in the Vale again.
Prince Daemon.

446
00:32:07.050 --> 00:32:09.970
What after the tragic death
of your first wife.

447
00:32:11.513 --> 00:32:14.283
And yet I receive raven after
raven from my bannermen

448
00:32:14.307 --> 00:32:17.203
informing me of your progress
throughout my domain.

449
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:18.579
Hm.

450
00:32:18.603 --> 00:32:21.106
Time heals even
the deepest of wounds.

451
00:32:23.150 --> 00:32:26.027
I am most delighted
to return. my lady.

452
00:32:28.405 --> 00:32:32.885
And who could ever fail to be
charmed by your... warmth.

453
00:32:32.909 --> 00:32:34.679
But I mustn't tarry.

454
00:32:34.703 --> 00:32:37.890
You promised the crown men
in return for a dragon.

455
00:32:37.914 --> 00:32:40.250
Now. you had your dragon.
yet we have no men.

456
00:32:42.252 --> 00:32:44.439
I should send babes.

457
00:32:44.463 --> 00:32:46.023
Prince Joffrey's dragon
was years away

458
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:47.942
from being large enough
to defend the Vale.

459
00:32:47.966 --> 00:32:49.676
and Rhaenyra took
even that away.

460
00:32:50.594 --> 00:32:52.405
A less forbearing person

461
00:32:52.429 --> 00:32:54.407
might have seen the
crown's offering as an insult.

462
00:32:54.431 --> 00:32:57.243
-A pledge is a pledge.
-It was my understanding

463
00:32:57.267 --> 00:32:59.328
that the war was won. my prince.

464
00:32:59.352 --> 00:33:02.772
What need does she have
of more soldiers?

465
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:05.650
In truth...

466
00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:09.630
I have not come for men.
I've come for gold.

467
00:33:09.654 --> 00:33:11.757
Huh. so your coffers are empty?

468
00:33:11.781 --> 00:33:13.217
The work of Hightower treachery.

469
00:33:13.241 --> 00:33:15.052
But perhaps a generous
offering of coin

470
00:33:15.076 --> 00:33:16.620
would demonstrate your...

471
00:33:17.787 --> 00:33:19.974
fealty to the crown.

472
00:33:19.998 --> 00:33:23.603
Prince Daemon Targaryen.
standing in my high hall.

473
00:33:23.627 --> 00:33:25.795
a beggar with a tin cup.

474
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.275
I never thought I'd live
to see such a sight.

475
00:33:29.299 --> 00:33:31.277
A gift of gold
would offer you the benefit

476
00:33:31.301 --> 00:33:32.886
of my speedy departure.

477
00:33:38.391 --> 00:33:39.785
Very well.

478
00:33:45.815 --> 00:33:48.235
Hey!

479
00:33:55.033 --> 00:33:56.326
Hey!

480
00:35:10.400 --> 00:35:12.027
Reveal yourself!

481
00:35:36.760 --> 00:35:38.637
Rhaena.

482
00:35:58.031 --> 00:36:00.092
<i>-Lykiri!
-Daor.</i>

483
00:36:00.116 --> 00:36:01.594
<i>Lykiri.</i>

484
00:36:11.586 --> 00:36:13.838
What have you done to yourself?

485
00:36:19.219 --> 00:36:20.970
How?

486
00:36:23.640 --> 00:36:25.117
I fed him sheep.

487
00:36:28.937 --> 00:36:31.337
Rhaenyra believes this dragon
and his rider are the reason...

488
00:36:33.650 --> 00:36:35.318
Jace is dead.

489
00:36:39.656 --> 00:36:41.926
-I wanted only to help.
-No.

490
00:36:41.950 --> 00:36:44.744
To show her... to show you
I... I never intended...

491
00:36:46.538 --> 00:36:49.165
Does she suffer?

492
00:36:51.376 --> 00:36:53.229
Jeyne Arryn knows you're here.

493
00:36:53.253 --> 00:36:55.106
You were meant to accompany
my sons to Pentos.

494
00:36:55.130 --> 00:36:56.732
They are well attended.
They will be safe.

495
00:36:56.756 --> 00:36:58.984
-You swore to be their guardian.
-And do what?

496
00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:03.346
Teach them to be ladies
of the realm?

497
00:37:04.514 --> 00:37:06.325
I would be of no use there.

498
00:37:06.349 --> 00:37:08.393
Just as I was of no use here.

499
00:37:12.021 --> 00:37:14.875
If you go now to where
you are meant to be.

500
00:37:14.899 --> 00:37:16.085
Rhaenyra need not know.

501
00:37:16.109 --> 00:37:18.212
We will find a ship.
Leave the dragon behind.

502
00:37:18.236 --> 00:37:20.673
I will not leave him.

503
00:37:20.697 --> 00:37:21.924
He's not like the others.
Rhaena.

504
00:37:21.948 --> 00:37:23.676
He is wild.
He cannot be trusted.

505
00:37:23.700 --> 00:37:26.035
He is mine. He is a part of me.

506
00:37:27.704 --> 00:37:29.414
I have been alone all my life.

507
00:37:31.374 --> 00:37:33.769
A Targaryen without a dragon.

508
00:37:33.793 --> 00:37:36.689
Disregarded. or... or worse.

509
00:37:36.713 --> 00:37:38.047
Pitied.

510
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:41.402
Can you yourself
say you ever gave me

511
00:37:41.426 --> 00:37:42.903
more than a passing thought?

512
00:37:42.927 --> 00:37:45.054
Rhaena. the unfortunate.

513
00:37:46.598 --> 00:37:48.892
Rhaena. the least
among your children.

514
00:37:52.562 --> 00:37:54.248
Come back with me. then.
to King's Landing.

515
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:55.899
-No.
-We will...

516
00:37:57.192 --> 00:37:59.545
speak to her together. We
will tell her it was a mistake.

517
00:37:59.569 --> 00:38:01.547
How can I ever stand
before her again

518
00:38:01.571 --> 00:38:03.740
after what I have done?

519
00:38:04.741 --> 00:38:06.844
No. I can never return.

520
00:38:06.868 --> 00:38:10.639
I will remain here.
alone and in exile.

521
00:38:10.663 --> 00:38:13.124
-That is my penance.
-She will hunt you down.

522
00:38:14.083 --> 00:38:15.394
Is hunting now.

523
00:38:15.418 --> 00:38:18.171
Let them grieve me
and think me lost to sea.

524
00:38:21.299 --> 00:38:23.235
Unless you betray me.

525
00:38:23.259 --> 00:38:25.404
You ask me to deceive her.
That is betrayal.

526
00:38:25.428 --> 00:38:29.015
I have asked you nothing.
Father. in all my life.

527
00:38:31.184 --> 00:38:32.912
I ask this one thing of you now.

528
00:38:32.936 --> 00:38:34.663
Rhaena. Rhaena.

529
00:38:34.687 --> 00:38:35.939
Rhaena!

530
00:38:37.982 --> 00:38:38.983
Rhaena!

531
00:38:55.458 --> 00:38:57.460
Shh!

532
00:39:40.837 --> 00:39:43.732
A raven just arrived
from Harrenhal. my lord.

533
00:39:43.756 --> 00:39:46.342
It bears the Hightower seal.

534
00:40:10.575 --> 00:40:12.035
Get out.

535
00:40:12.785 --> 00:40:14.513
My prince?

536
00:40:14.537 --> 00:40:16.372
Out. Now.

537
00:40:28.551 --> 00:40:31.947
Useless craven coward!

538
00:40:31.971 --> 00:40:34.074
Cunt!

539
00:40:36.601 --> 00:40:38.913
Cunt! Cunt!

540
00:40:38.937 --> 00:40:40.873
Cunt!

541
00:41:09.467 --> 00:41:11.761
Your Uncle Gwayne has sent word.

542
00:41:13.846 --> 00:41:15.741
It seems your brother Aemond

543
00:41:15.765 --> 00:41:18.101
will not be joining us
after all.

544
00:41:20.687 --> 00:41:22.313
Is...

545
00:41:23.606 --> 00:41:25.483
Gwayne coming to Tumbleton?

546
00:41:28.194 --> 00:41:30.113
We must alter our scheme.

547
00:41:34.617 --> 00:41:37.217
<i>Ser Otto wrote diligently to Ormund.</i>

548
00:41:37.954 --> 00:41:39.598
Naught was returned.

549
00:41:39.622 --> 00:41:42.101
Are you sure
there's been no error?

550
00:41:42.125 --> 00:41:43.126
Nothing?

551
00:41:45.795 --> 00:41:47.296
What am I to make of this?

552
00:41:48.673 --> 00:41:51.568
I suppose only that Lord Ormund

553
00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:54.971
ruled Oldtown
as a kingdom unto itself.

554
00:41:55.930 --> 00:41:56.930
Mm.

555
00:42:14.824 --> 00:42:18.137
Ser Ulf White is still
without. Your Grace.

556
00:42:18.161 --> 00:42:19.328
Oh. uh...

557
00:42:20.538 --> 00:42:21.539
Come.

558
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:25.084
Your Grace.

559
00:42:26.669 --> 00:42:29.231
I'm honored
to be in your service

560
00:42:29.255 --> 00:42:32.484
and to have sworn my life
to your cause.

561
00:42:32.508 --> 00:42:33.551
Yes. I'm sure.

562
00:42:34.552 --> 00:42:37.656
-What is it. then?
-Oh. I... I wondered

563
00:42:37.680 --> 00:42:41.118
whether. as Your Grace's
humble servant.

564
00:42:41.142 --> 00:42:44.562
I might petition
for your favor... er. favors.

565
00:42:45.354 --> 00:42:46.832
Speak them.

566
00:42:46.856 --> 00:42:50.085
For a man named Mujja.

567
00:42:50.109 --> 00:42:54.173
a smallholding outside Rosby

568
00:42:54.197 --> 00:42:56.759
and exemption from taxes.
thanking Your Grace.

569
00:42:56.783 --> 00:42:59.094
And for a fellow named Cley.

570
00:42:59.118 --> 00:43:02.681
a pardon for various
small crimes.

571
00:43:02.705 --> 00:43:04.683
We don't have to go into that.
and passage to Lys...

572
00:43:04.707 --> 00:43:06.351
These favors
are not in your name.

573
00:43:06.375 --> 00:43:08.211
No. no. Your Grace.

574
00:43:10.046 --> 00:43:11.464
They're for allies...

575
00:43:12.799 --> 00:43:14.860
from a tavern I frequent... ed.

576
00:43:14.884 --> 00:43:17.386
-frequented previously.
-A tavern.

577
00:43:19.597 --> 00:43:23.744
And if an agent
of the Hightowers

578
00:43:23.768 --> 00:43:26.038
knifes you in your belly
as you fill it with ale?

579
00:43:26.062 --> 00:43:28.606
No. it's not that sort of place.
Besides...

580
00:43:31.067 --> 00:43:34.046
-It's my belly.
-Oh. but it's not.

581
00:43:34.070 --> 00:43:37.299
No. you belong now to the crown.

582
00:43:37.323 --> 00:43:40.052
Should something
befall you or your belly.

583
00:43:40.076 --> 00:43:41.887
I suffer the loss of a dragon

584
00:43:41.911 --> 00:43:44.014
and the unity of the realm
is threatened.

585
00:43:44.038 --> 00:43:47.226
No. you shall frequent
taverns no longer.

586
00:43:47.250 --> 00:43:48.769
What?

587
00:43:48.793 --> 00:43:51.021
Well. I'm afraid you'll
have to find your...

588
00:43:51.045 --> 00:43:53.398
your beer within the walls
of the Red Keep.

589
00:43:53.422 --> 00:43:56.151
where you will remain...

590
00:43:56.175 --> 00:43:58.237
except when you are escorted
to the Dragonpit

591
00:43:58.261 --> 00:43:59.512
for duty at Tumbleton.

592
00:44:00.847 --> 00:44:02.932
If that is all. you may go.

593
00:44:12.900 --> 00:44:14.152
They protest you.

594
00:44:15.319 --> 00:44:18.281
You know. out there in the city.

595
00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:22.201
I've seen vile words
painted on walls.

596
00:44:23.995 --> 00:44:25.163
They say...

597
00:44:26.789 --> 00:44:28.207
"Queen of Bastards."

598
00:44:31.961 --> 00:44:34.273
The work. I am sure.

599
00:44:34.297 --> 00:44:36.859
of some of your
misguided subjects

600
00:44:36.883 --> 00:44:40.052
who mistakenly believe
their queen to be unkind.

601
00:44:44.974 --> 00:44:46.225
Your Grace.

602
00:45:04.869 --> 00:45:06.972
Can you send word to Ser Luthor?

603
00:45:06.996 --> 00:45:10.475
Have his gold cloaks look
for any seditious markings

604
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:12.376
on the streets of the city.
remove them...

605
00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:15.296
and find those responsible.

606
00:45:16.005 --> 00:45:17.316
And bring them to you.
Your Grace?

607
00:45:17.340 --> 00:45:20.009
Just make it cease. please.

608
00:45:40.905 --> 00:45:43.950
There's a Braavosi cog sailing
from Duskendale in a few days.

609
00:45:44.867 --> 00:45:47.221
-I think I can find us fresh horses.
-I'm the fucking king.

610
00:45:47.245 --> 00:45:49.085
If they knew I walked among them.

611
00:45:49.914 --> 00:45:52.851
Even were you to be believed.
Rhaenyra sits the throne.

612
00:45:52.875 --> 00:45:54.603
And you have no dragon.

613
00:45:54.627 --> 00:45:57.046
She did us a favor
by declaring you dead.

614
00:45:59.548 --> 00:46:00.609
I'm dead?

615
00:46:00.633 --> 00:46:02.134
Slain by your brother Aemond.

616
00:46:03.427 --> 00:46:05.197
Is that what they say?

617
00:46:05.221 --> 00:46:06.865
Mm.

618
00:46:06.889 --> 00:46:07.991
I'll fucking kill him.

619
00:46:08.015 --> 00:46:10.101
-I'll fucking kill her. the s...
-In time.

620
00:46:12.311 --> 00:46:14.873
There's much to be learned
from the chatter in this camp.

621
00:46:14.897 --> 00:46:18.651
Anonymity is a boon for us.

622
00:46:19.402 --> 00:46:23.739
It will ensure that your
eventual resurrection...

623
00:46:26.242 --> 00:46:28.244
becomes the stuff
of song and legend.

624
00:46:32.164 --> 00:46:33.582
Have something to eat.

625
00:46:42.341 --> 00:46:43.902
None left for us.

626
00:46:43.926 --> 00:46:45.303
Happens sometimes. but...

627
00:46:46.262 --> 00:46:48.931
We'll get some tomorrow.

628
00:46:49.640 --> 00:46:51.100
Tomorrow?

629
00:46:54.103 --> 00:46:56.248
I'll not stand for this.

630
00:46:56.272 --> 00:46:58.065
Outrage!

631
00:46:59.358 --> 00:47:01.652
Is this how you rule?
Running out of food?

632
00:47:04.447 --> 00:47:06.115
Answer me!

633
00:47:07.116 --> 00:47:09.845
Sit down before I make you.

634
00:47:09.869 --> 00:47:11.221
Who do you think
you're talking to?

635
00:47:11.245 --> 00:47:13.125
I'll have your fucking tongue.
you insolent ape.

636
00:47:13.956 --> 00:47:15.309
-Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
-Please.

637
00:47:15.333 --> 00:47:19.104
And I'll gut you
like a fish. cunt.

638
00:47:19.128 --> 00:47:21.964
Let's... let's not be hasty.

639
00:47:26.302 --> 00:47:28.113
On your knees.

640
00:47:28.137 --> 00:47:29.388
if you want to live.

641
00:47:54.205 --> 00:47:55.831
Kiss my feet.

642
00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:00.354
-I take it back.
-Or die.

643
00:48:00.378 --> 00:48:01.545
I don't care which.

644
00:48:04.006 --> 00:48:05.674
But you will call me...

645
00:48:06.425 --> 00:48:08.737
-"my lord."
-Janos.

646
00:48:08.761 --> 00:48:10.179
You as well?

647
00:48:37.123 --> 00:48:39.226
The inquisitions were thorough.

648
00:48:39.250 --> 00:48:41.436
We should be assured
that wherever they might be.

649
00:48:41.460 --> 00:48:43.355
the crown's holdings...

650
00:48:43.379 --> 00:48:46.132
-are no longer in...
-I bring justice.

651
00:48:50.886 --> 00:48:52.388
I bring vengeance.

652
00:48:53.973 --> 00:48:55.349
I also bring gold.

653
00:48:57.726 --> 00:49:01.081
-What is this?
-The one who rode Sheep stealer.

654
00:49:01.105 --> 00:49:05.443
Along with 10.000 golden dragons
from Lady Jeyne Arryn.

655
00:49:07.695 --> 00:49:09.695
Anything from
her bannermen in the Vale?

656
00:49:10.781 --> 00:49:13.260
We still await some response
from the great houses.

657
00:49:13.284 --> 00:49:16.138
And the Iron Bank has not
answered our request for a loan.

658
00:49:16.162 --> 00:49:18.181
Would you please explain
who that is?

659
00:49:18.205 --> 00:49:21.893
Ser Torrhen Manderly.
my prince. the new Master of Coin.

660
00:49:21.917 --> 00:49:24.146
What little there is
to be a master of.

661
00:49:24.170 --> 00:49:26.773
Well. I'll wager you think you're
clever. don't you. Manderly?

662
00:49:26.797 --> 00:49:28.108
-Well...
-You should know

663
00:49:28.132 --> 00:49:29.675
I'm the clever one around here.

664
00:49:31.719 --> 00:49:33.780
-Say no more.
-What small quantity

665
00:49:33.804 --> 00:49:37.284
of gold Daemon has found
must go to ease the deprivations

666
00:49:37.308 --> 00:49:39.286
-of the smallfolk.
-The City Watch is stretched far too thin.

667
00:49:39.310 --> 00:49:40.787
Our soldiers need to be paid

668
00:49:40.811 --> 00:49:43.331
and more recruited besides.
else there will be bedlam.

669
00:49:43.355 --> 00:49:44.749
-Your Grace...
-Bedlam is assured

670
00:49:44.773 --> 00:49:46.334
if the people feel the crown
ignores their anger.

671
00:49:46.358 --> 00:49:48.670
Has anyone considered a tax?

672
00:49:48.694 --> 00:49:50.362
Clear the room.

673
00:50:07.213 --> 00:50:08.380
What is this?

674
00:50:10.257 --> 00:50:11.485
The queen's justice.

675
00:50:11.509 --> 00:50:12.843
Who is he?

676
00:50:13.886 --> 00:50:16.281
And how did he come
to claim a wild dragon?

677
00:50:16.305 --> 00:50:18.658
Was he alone. or is...

678
00:50:18.682 --> 00:50:21.244
is he allied to Aemond
or to Ormund?

679
00:50:21.268 --> 00:50:22.787
I desired the very same answers.

680
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:24.539
but a dragon is not
a precise instrument.

681
00:50:24.563 --> 00:50:27.209
What of Sheep stealer?

682
00:50:27.233 --> 00:50:29.377
Fled. Riderless.

683
00:50:29.401 --> 00:50:31.296
It is an act of madness
to claim a wild dragon.

684
00:50:31.320 --> 00:50:32.863
We are not like to see it again.

685
00:50:39.662 --> 00:50:42.831
I wanted to see him.

686
00:50:47.002 --> 00:50:51.048
I wanted to look on the one
who killed my son.

687
00:50:55.344 --> 00:50:56.971
To punish him yourself?

688
00:50:59.515 --> 00:51:01.725
But do you think
that would end your grief?

689
00:51:02.685 --> 00:51:04.311
I have served your interest.

690
00:51:15.698 --> 00:51:19.118
The gold you brought will
provide alms for the smallfolk.

691
00:51:20.327 --> 00:51:23.205
The City Watch trusts you. You
will entreat them to be patient.

692
00:51:24.540 --> 00:51:26.542
The crown will honor its debt...

693
00:51:27.543 --> 00:51:28.877
a little longer.

694
00:51:35.217 --> 00:51:36.385
I suppose...

695
00:51:37.720 --> 00:51:39.388
I should thank you.

696
00:51:48.606 --> 00:51:52.377
When what you've wrought
comes falling down about her ears.

697
00:51:52.401 --> 00:51:55.070
she'll return to her senses.

698
00:51:55.779 --> 00:51:57.364
Whose head is that?

699
00:52:37.112 --> 00:52:40.425
I have dispatched good men
to see your father's remains

700
00:52:40.449 --> 00:52:41.992
delivered to Oldtown.

701
00:52:50.376 --> 00:52:51.835
Viserys would have wished it.

702
00:52:54.672 --> 00:52:55.881
Thank you.

703
00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:19.071
Here.

704
00:53:31.834 --> 00:53:33.335
Helaena.

705
00:53:38.841 --> 00:53:40.860
Clear the streets.

706
00:53:40.884 --> 00:53:42.362
Clear the streets!

707
00:53:42.386 --> 00:53:44.722
Observe the curfew!

708
00:53:47.850 --> 00:53:49.268
All indoors!

709
00:53:51.186 --> 00:53:52.688
Clear the street!

710
00:53:55.190 --> 00:53:57.877
Stay home or hang!

711
00:53:57.901 --> 00:53:59.903
Dragon!

712
00:54:00.237 --> 00:54:01.363
Dragon!

713
00:54:26.889 --> 00:54:29.951
Open your doors by order of the queen.

714
00:54:29.975 --> 00:54:32.227
Here! Here!

715
00:54:33.395 --> 00:54:34.789
-With me.
-Up here.

716
00:54:34.813 --> 00:54:36.875
Get them out of their home!

717
00:54:36.899 --> 00:54:38.066
Who did this?

718
00:54:39.234 --> 00:54:41.171
Which traitor
stained these walls?

719
00:54:41.195 --> 00:54:42.922
Find the hand that
stained these walls.

720
00:54:42.946 --> 00:54:44.382
Scrub. Scrub!

721
00:54:46.909 --> 00:54:48.076
Bring them out!

722
00:55:09.306 --> 00:55:11.743
-Has he confessed?
-Not yet.

723
00:55:11.767 --> 00:55:14.144
I haven't done anything. Please.

724
00:55:15.604 --> 00:55:16.772
Please.

725
00:55:17.898 --> 00:55:21.169
Patience. my girl.

726
00:55:21.193 --> 00:55:23.445
It won't be long before
we can fly again.

727
00:55:27.241 --> 00:55:29.677
I have warned you
against indulging in affection

728
00:55:29.701 --> 00:55:31.137
for that beast.

729
00:55:33.455 --> 00:55:34.706
<i>Lykiri.</i>

730
00:55:39.962 --> 00:55:41.547
I know.

731
00:55:51.306 --> 00:55:52.724
You are a good boy.

732
00:55:54.393 --> 00:55:57.062
You speak kindly
and you say your prayers.

733
00:55:58.230 --> 00:56:00.041
I have raised you
in the light of the Seven.

734
00:56:00.065 --> 00:56:01.942
and the Father smiles upon you.

735
00:56:03.902 --> 00:56:05.988
But there is a taint
in your blood.

736
00:56:07.489 --> 00:56:10.301
The Targaryens
are a savage race.

737
00:56:10.325 --> 00:56:12.494
poor in intellect.
but rich in cunning.

738
00:56:14.246 --> 00:56:17.141
With dark spells.
they created abominations

739
00:56:17.165 --> 00:56:19.001
to subdue what was rightly ours.

740
00:56:22.963 --> 00:56:24.590
We are the superior men.

741
00:56:25.674 --> 00:56:27.986
But against that...

742
00:56:29.761 --> 00:56:31.179
We could not stand.

743
00:56:39.730 --> 00:56:42.441
The gods have put you
to divine purpose. my boy.

744
00:56:43.483 --> 00:56:45.527
What purpose. sire?

745
00:56:46.862 --> 00:56:50.574
The brutes raise a woman
to the Iron Throne.

746
00:56:51.408 --> 00:56:52.594
A desecration!

747
00:56:52.618 --> 00:56:55.370
Where is reason?
Where is propriety?

748
00:56:56.371 --> 00:56:58.540
It was a blessing that you
came to ward in Oldtown.

749
00:56:59.541 --> 00:57:01.960
Your brothers are lost.
but you...

750
00:57:02.961 --> 00:57:05.064
remain a Hightower.

751
00:57:05.088 --> 00:57:07.483
raised in the shadow
of the Citadel.

752
00:57:07.507 --> 00:57:09.927
in the light of the Starry Sept.

753
00:57:14.932 --> 00:57:15.933
Now...

754
00:57:17.100 --> 00:57:18.727
you must be king.

755
00:57:23.899 --> 00:57:26.210
You would not wish. surely.

756
00:57:26.234 --> 00:57:28.713
for me to turn cloak
against my brothers.

757
00:57:28.737 --> 00:57:31.049
You will restore
our ancient order.

758
00:57:31.073 --> 00:57:33.992
Victory will be ours.
It is the will of the gods.

759
00:57:36.244 --> 00:57:37.788
I thought you let him go.

760
00:57:38.747 --> 00:57:40.475
A righteous king
must demonstrate

761
00:57:40.499 --> 00:57:42.602
he upholds many virtues.

762
00:57:42.626 --> 00:57:44.336
Honor. wisdom.

763
00:57:45.420 --> 00:57:48.399
-Justice.
-He only acted when our man attacked a woman.

764
00:57:48.423 --> 00:57:50.193
He laid hands on a Hightower.

765
00:57:50.217 --> 00:57:53.488
That soldier is an extension
of you. of the crown.

766
00:57:53.512 --> 00:57:55.073
Justice must be done.

767
00:57:55.097 --> 00:57:57.283
Is not mercy a kingly virtue?

768
00:57:57.307 --> 00:57:59.619
That sounds like something
your father would say.

769
00:58:03.939 --> 00:58:05.273
I'm sorry.

770
00:58:27.254 --> 00:58:30.132
I have risked much
and more to raise you up.

771
00:58:31.967 --> 00:58:34.011
Surely. you do not wish
to disappoint me.

772
00:58:50.986 --> 00:58:52.714
My lord.

773
00:58:52.738 --> 00:58:55.299
My lord. please. Please.

774
00:58:55.323 --> 00:58:57.844
No. please. I beg you.

775
00:58:57.868 --> 00:58:59.244
